1. Accept a string from the user and print the first middle and last character in a string.

2. Accept two strings from a user and also 3rd string and append the third string between first and second.

3. Explained array in Python:
 -> An array is a collection of items stored in a contiguous memory location.
 ->It is easy to calculate the position of each element by simply adding an offset of a base value.
 ->Python does not have built-in support for arrays, but Python list can be used instead.
 -> If you want to create an array in Python we have to use the below syntax

      Array_Name = array('Type_code',[Elements])


    
